    <text>
        <body>
            <head>243. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="recgt3SoCfObWa7Tt">Powell</persName>) to President
                    Reagan<note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d243fn1">Source: <orgName
                        corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security Council</orgName>, National
                    Security Council Institutional Files, Box SR096, NSDD 290. Top Secret. Sent for
                    action. Drafted by <persName corresp="rec3WaAgwEDeqcFLV">Linhard</persName>.
                    Copied to <persName corresp="recjlYSNpDHCqlk6w">Bush</persName> and Senator
                        <persName corresp="recEQQb67MTNPG0x8">Baker</persName>. A stamped notation
                    at the top of the memorandum indicates that <persName
                        corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> saw the memorandum on December
                    7. Another stamped notation on the memorandum reads: “Signed.”</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1987-12-07"
                        >December 7, 1987</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Proposed NSDD on <rs type="topic" corresp="recPup8iFysWzHs3K">Arms
                        Control</rs> Positions for <rs type="event" corresp="recXjSFzYsuO3Q5ns"
                            >US-<gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss> Summit</rs>
                </item>
            </list>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
            <p>Whether you should sign the proposed NSDD<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d243fn2"
                    >Printed below as <ref target="#d244">Document 244</ref>.</note> at <hi
                    rendition="simple_italic">TAB A</hi> establishing the United States Government
                position on <rs type="topic" corresp="recPup8iFysWzHs3K">Arms Control</rs> subjects
                for the December 8–10, 1987 summit meeting with Soviet General Secretary <persName
                    corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">Gorbachev</persName>.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Background</p>
            <p>After extended discussion with your cabinet and other senior US officials,
                recommendations on <rs type="topic" corresp="recPup8iFysWzHs3K">arms control</rs>
                positions with the Soviets have become clear. The proposed NSDD reflects both those
                recommendations and your own views as expressed in the meetings in preparation for
                the summit.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
            <p>Before summit and other important meetings, an NSDD codifying the discussions,
                recommendations, and consensus positions of the United States Government is very
                useful. It documents the origin of the US positions, and also provides clear
                guidance for the working groups and other meetings with the Soviets that will occur
                during the summit period.</p>
            <pb facs="1095" n="1068" xml:id="pg_1068"/>
            <p>In accordance with NSDD 266,<note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d243fn3">NSDD 266,
                    “Implementation of the Recommendations of the President’s Special Review Board,”
                    is scheduled for publication in <ref target="frus1981-88v02">
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1981–1988, vol. II,
                        Organization and Management of Foreign Policy</ref>.</note> the <gloss
                    target="#t_NSC_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">NSC</orgName>
                </gloss> Legal Advisor has coordinated the attached NSDD with A.B. Culvahouse in
                advance of its submission to you.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
            <table cols="2">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="#roman">OK</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="#roman">No</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>________</cell>
                    <cell>________</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="#roman">That you sign the proposed NSDD at</hi>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">TAB A</hi>.<note n="4" place="foot"
                            xml:id="d243fn4">
                            <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> initialed his
                            approval.</note>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </table>
        </body>
    </text>
